.TH "ethnl_bitmap32_update" 9 "ethnl_bitmap32_update" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
ethnl_bitmap32_update \- Modify u32 based bitmap according to value/mask pair
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "void" ethnl_bitmap32_update
.BI "(u32 *dst "  ","
.BI "unsigned int nbits "  ","
.BI "const u32 *value "  ","
.BI "const u32 *mask "  ","
.BI "bool *mod "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "dst" 12
bitmap to update
.IP "nbits" 12
bit size of the bitmap
.IP "value" 12
values to set
.IP "mask" 12
mask of bits to set
.IP "mod" 12
set to true if bitmap is modified, preserve if not
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
Set bits in \fIdst\fP bitmap which are set in \fImask\fP to values from \fIvalue\fP, leave
the rest untouched. If destination bitmap was modified, set \fImod\fP to true,
leave as it is if not.
